The paper proposes a new method for rhythm classification of ECG records using high-level features and a Recurrent Neural Network. This involves machine learning techniques such as classification and feature extraction, which are commonly associated with sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of a neural network suggests a possible association with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the use of morphological and rhythm-related features, which could be related to sub-categories such as cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
